almost thought was--

00:40:40.350 --> 00:40:42.480 align:middle line:84%
this is just how this
place is, not understanding

00:40:42.480 --> 00:40:45.110 align:middle line:84%
that this place had
been kind of gardened

00:40:45.110 --> 00:40:47.090 align:middle line:90%
for thousands of years, right?

00:40:47.090 --> 00:40:50.210 align:middle line:84%
Something like the first people
who came to North America

00:40:50.210 --> 00:40:53.780 align:middle line:84%
were thinking probably
14,000 to 20,000 years ago,

00:40:53.780 --> 00:40:56.210 align:middle line:84%
they migrated over
when there was still

00:40:56.210 --> 00:40:57.650 align:middle line:90%
an ice sheet connect--

00:40:57.650 --> 00:41:00.750 align:middle line:84%
and also those ice sheets had
to drop to the water level.

00:41:00.750 --> 00:41:04.290 align:middle line:84%
So the Bering Strait was this
massive open land bridge.

00:41:04.290 --> 00:41:05.540 align:middle line:90%
Not like a narrow land bridge.

00:41:05.540 --> 00:41:07.070 align:middle line:84%
We're talking
1,000 miles of land

00:41:07.070 --> 00:41:08.450 align:middle line:90%
