00:41:29.000 --> 00:41:29.958 align:middle line:90%
That's all that's left.

00:41:29.958 --> 00:41:31.670 align:middle line:84%
Like we ate down
through it, right?

00:41:31.670 --> 00:41:33.568 align:middle line:84%
So it's like an
inverted trophic scale

00:41:33.568 --> 00:41:36.110 align:middle line:84%
where we took all the big stuff,
and then when that was gone,

00:41:36.110 --> 00:41:36.920 align:middle line:90%
we took the next thing.

00:41:36.920 --> 00:41:38.878 align:middle line:84%
And when that was gone,
we took the next thing.

00:41:38.878 --> 00:41:40.747 align:middle line:84%
And now we're
running out of stuff.

00:41:40.747 --> 00:41:42.080 align:middle line:90%
We're eating our way through it.

00:41:42.080 --> 00:41:45.100 align:middle line:84%
We've become the opposite
